# Clean Architecture — Microserviços

> Skill detalhada: `.cursor/skills/clean-architecture/SKILL.md`

## Camadas (de dentro para fora)

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Presentation["presentation/"]
        CTRL[Controllers · Guards · Modules]
    end
    subgraph Application["application/"]
        UC[Use Cases · DTOs]
    end
    subgraph Domain["domain/"]
        ENT[Entities · Ports · Constants]
    end
    subgraph Infrastructure["infrastructure/"]
        ADAPT[Adapters · Repositories]
    end

    CTRL --> UC
    UC --> ENT
    UC --> PORTS[Ports]
    ADAPT -.implements.-> PORTS
```

## Regras

- **Domain** não importa de application, infrastructure ou presentation
- **Application** depende apenas de domain
- **Infrastructure** implementa interfaces definidas em domain/application
- **Presentation** orquestra use cases via injeção de dependência

## Exemplo de Use Case

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class SendMessageUseCase {
  constructor(
    @Inject(AI_PORT) private readonly aiPort: AiPort,
    @Inject(CONVERSATION_STORE) private readonly conversationRepo: ConversationRepository,
  ) {}

  async execute(dto: SendMessageDto): Promise<MessageResponse> {
    const conversation = await this.conversationRepo.findOrCreate(dto.sessionId);
    return this.aiPort.generateResponse(conversation, dto.message);
  }
}
```

## Nomenclatura

- Use cases: `{Verbo}{Entidade}UseCase` (ex: `AuthenticateUserUseCase`)
- Ports: `{Entidade}Port` ou `{Entidade}Repository`
- DTOs: `{Ação}{Entidade}Dto`
